{{!--
/**
 * Player Spell Book Tab Navigation Template
 *
 * PURPOSE:
 * Navigation interface for switching between different spell book tabs including
 * class-specific spell preparation tabs and wizard spellbook management. Provides
 * visual tab switching with support for both icon-based and image-based tab
 * representations, particularly for multiclass character management.
 *
 * CONTEXT REQUIREMENTS:
 * @param {boolean} hasMultipleTabs - Whether multiple tabs should be displayed
 * @param {Array<Object>} tabs - Collection of available tab configurations
 * @param {string} tabs[].id - Unique tab identifier for navigation targeting
 * @param {string} tabs[].group - Tab group identifier for coordinated navigation
 * @param {string} tabs[].cssClass - CSS classes for tab styling and state
 * @param {string} tabs[].label - Display label for tab (used in tooltips)
 * @param {string} tabs[].icon - Icon CSS classes for tab display (optional)
 * @param {Object} tabs[].data - Additional tab data object (optional)
 * @param {string} tabs[].data.classImg - Class-specific image path for visual tabs (optional)
 *
 * ACCESSIBILITY FEATURES:
 * - Navigation element with semantic nav tag for landmark navigation
 * - Tab elements with proper data-action and data-tab attributes
 * - Tooltip attributes for additional context on hover
 * - Alt text for class image icons describing the tab purpose
 * - Icon elements marked as decorative with proper CSS classes
 *
 * CUSTOMIZATION POINTS:
 * - Tab display conditionally shows only when multiple tabs exist
 * - Tab icons support both CSS icon classes and custom class images
 * - Tab styling adapts through CSS classes for active/inactive states
 * - Tab positioning uses tabs-right class for layout control
 * - Visual tab representation switches between icons and images based on data
 *
 * INTEGRATION:
 * - Connects to PlayerSpellBook application tab management system
 * - Uses data-group="spellbook-tabs" for coordinated tab behavior
 * - Supports both standard spellcasting and wizard-specific tabs
 * - Integrates with Foundry VTT's tab navigation system
 * - Works with application's tab state management and rendering
 */
--}}

<nav class="tabs tabs-right" data-group="spellbook-tabs">
  {{#if hasMultipleTabs}}
    {{#each tabs as |tab|}}
      <!-- Individual Tab Navigation Item - Supports icons and class images -->
      <a class="item {{tab.cssClass}}" data-action="tab" data-tab="{{tab.id}}" data-group="{{tab.group}}"
        data-tooltip="{{tab.label}}">

        {{#if tab.data.classImg}}
          <!-- Class-Specific Image Icon - For visual class representation -->
          <img src="{{tab.data.classImg}}" alt="{{tab.label}}" class="tab-icon">
        {{else if tab.icon}}
          <!-- CSS Icon - Standard icon fonts for generic tabs -->
          <i class="{{tab.icon}}"></i>
        {{/if}}
      </a>
    {{/each}}
  {{/if}}
</nav>
